Definition: in a singular manner or to a singular degree
Example: Lord T. was considered singularly licentious even for the courts of Russia and Portugal; he acquired three wives and fourteen children during his Portuguese embassy alone
Synonyms: adj, all, extraordinary, singular, in, a, manner, or, to, degree, Lord, T, was, considered, licentious, even, for, the, courts, of, Russia, and, Portugal, he, acquired, three, wives, fourteen, children, during, his, Portuguese, embassy, alone
Category: adv.all
